===Proper Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Darth]] Vader'''

#A main character in George Lucas's movie, ''Star Wars.'' (41.9 [[BBY]] - 4 [[ABY]]) The Dark Lord of the [[Sith]] and brutal apprentice to [[Darth Sidious]].  In 19 BBY, [[Anakin Skywalker]] was dubbed Darth Vader when he turned to the dark side of the Force.

===Etymology===
'''Dar'''k Lord of the Si'''th''' forms Darth, Vader is the cut form of In'''vader''', sometimes connected to the Dutch word for [[father]]. Since the idea of Luke Skywalker being Vader's son came only while filming the ''Empire Strikes Back'', this Dutch-relation is an invalid speculation.

